msgstr "Monks’ Confession 14"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:0.5"
msgid "14. Senāsanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on furniture"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc14.1.1, pts-vp-en.2.238, ms2V_380
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū hemantike kāle ajjhokāse senāsanaṃ paññapetvā kāyaṃ otāpentā kāle ārocite taṃ pakkamantā neva uddhariṃsu na uddharāpesuṃ, anāpucchā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr "At that time it was winter, and the monks put furniture out in the open in order to warm themselves in the sun. But when the time for departure was announced, they left without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.3"
msgid "Senāsanaṃ ovaṭṭhaṃ hoti."
msgstr "And the furniture was rained on."

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.4"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.5"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.6"
msgid "“kathaṃ hi nāma bhikkhū ajjhokāse senāsanaṃ paññapetvā taṃ pakkamantā neva uddharissanti na uddharāpessanti, anāpucchā pakkamissanti, senāsanaṃ ovaṭṭhan”ti."
msgstr "“How can those monks put furniture out in the open and then leave without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone? The furniture was rained on.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_381
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.7"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.8"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ajjhokāse … pe …"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.9"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.9a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_382, pts-vp-en.2.239
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.10"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu saṃghikaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā bhisiṃ vā kocchaṃ vā ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk takes a bed, a bench, a mattress, or a stool belonging to the Order and puts it out in the open or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away, getting it put away, or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_383
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.1.11"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.40, pts-cs-bu-pc14.1.2, ms2V_384
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ajjhokāse vasitvā kālasseva senāsanaṃ abhiharanti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards monks who had stayed out in the open brought the furniture back even though it was not the rainy season."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.2.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā te bhikkhū kālasseva senāsanaṃ abhiharante."
msgstr "The Master saw this,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.2.3"
msgid "Disvāna etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "and after giving a teaching, he addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: aṭṭha māse avassikasaṅkete → vasituṃ avassi­ka­saṃ­kete (itipi)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:1.2.4"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭha māse avassikasaṅkete maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā yattha kākā vā kulalā vā na ūhadanti tattha senāsanaṃ nikkhipitun”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, during the eight months outside of the rainy season, I allow you  to store furniture under a roof-cover or at the foot of a tree or wherever crows or ravens donʼt leave droppings.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-pc14.2.1, ms2V_385
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_386
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.6"
msgid "Saṃghikaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Belonging to the Order:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.7"
msgid "saṃghassa dinnaṃ hoti pariccattaṃ."
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc8, pts-vp-en.2.240, ms2V_387
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.8"
msgid "Mañco nāma"
msgstr "A bed:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.9"
msgid "cattāro mañcā—"
msgstr "there are four kinds of beds:"

#. HTML: _Masāraka_. Sp.2.111(VRI): _Masārakoti mañcapāde vijjhitvā tattha aṭaniyo pavesetvā kato_—“_Masāraka_: it is made by making a hole in the legs of the bed and then inserting the rails of the frame there.”
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.10"
msgid "masārako, bundikābaddho, kuḷīrapādako, āhaccapādako."
msgstr "one with legs and frame called _masāraka_, one with legs and frame called _bundikābaddha_, one with crooked legs, one with detachable legs."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_388
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.11"
msgid "Pīṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A bench:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.12"
msgid "cattāri pīṭhāni—"
msgstr "there are four kinds of benches:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.13"
msgid "masārakaṃ, bundikābaddhaṃ, kuḷīrapādakaṃ, āhaccapādakaṃ."
msgstr "one with legs and frame called _masāraka_, one with legs and frame called _bundikābaddha_, one with crooked legs, one with detachable legs."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_389
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.14"
msgid "Bhisi nāma"
msgstr "A mattress:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.15"
msgid "pañca bhisiyo—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of mattresses:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.16"
msgid "uṇṇabhisi, coḷabhisi, vākabhisi, tiṇabhisi, paṇṇabhisi."
msgstr "a mattress stuffed with wool, a mattress stuffed with cloth, a mattress stuffed with bark, a mattress stuffed with grass, a mattress stuffed with leaves."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_390
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.17"
msgid "Kocchaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "A stool:"

# NOTE: I have rendered khus-khus reed, _muñja_-reed, and _pabbaja_-reed with the single word “reed.” I am not aware that these types of reed can be properly distinguished in English.
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. VAR: pabbajamayaṃ → babbajamayaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.18"
msgid "vākamayaṃ vā usīramayaṃ vā muñjamayaṃ vā pabbajamayaṃ vā anto saṃveṭhetvā baddhaṃ hoti."
msgstr "one made of bark, one made of reed; it is upholstered and then bound together."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_391
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.19"
msgid "Santharitvāti"
msgstr "Puts […] out:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.20"
msgid "sayaṃ santharitvā."
msgstr "puts out oneself."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc13, pts-vp-en.2.241, ms2V_392
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.21"
msgid "Santharāpetvāti"
msgstr "Gets […] put out:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.22"
msgid "aññaṃ santharāpetvā."
msgstr "gets another to put out."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.23"
msgid "Anupasampannaṃ santharāpeti, tassa palibodho."
msgstr "If he gets one who is not fully ordained to put it out, it is the responsibility of the monk."

#. VAR: santhārakassa → santhatassa (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.24"
msgid "Upasampannaṃ santharāpeti, santhārakassa palibodho."
msgstr "If he gets one who is fully ordained to put it out, it is the responsibility of the one who puts it out."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc14, ms2V_393
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.25"
msgid "Taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyyāti"
msgstr "Leaves without putting it away:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.26"
msgid "na sayaṃ uddhareyya."
msgstr "he does not put it away himself."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc15, ms2V_394
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.27"
msgid "Na uddharāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Getting it put away:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.28"
msgid "na aññaṃ uddharāpeyya."
msgstr "he does not get another to put it away."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_395
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.29"
msgid "Anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyyāti"
msgstr "Or telling anyone:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.1.30"
msgid "bhikkhuṃ vā sāmaṇeraṃ vā ārāmikaṃ vā anāpucchā majjhimassa purisassa leḍḍupātaṃ atikkamantassa āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he does not tell a monk, a novice monk, or a monastery worker, then when he goes beyond the distance of a stone-throw of an average man, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc17, pts-cs-bu-pc14.2.2, ms2V_396
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.1"
msgid "Saṃghike saṃghikasaññī ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, and he puts it out in the open or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.2"
msgid "Saṃghike vematiko … pe …"
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.3"
msgid "saṃghike puggalikasaññī ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he puts it out in the open or gets it put out, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>_Cimilikā_. Sp.2.112(VRI): _Cimilikā nāma sudhādiparikammakatāya bhūmiyā vaṇṇānurakkhaṇatthaṃ katā hoti, taṃ heṭṭhā pattharitvā upari kaṭasārakaṃ pattharanti_—“A _cimilikā_ is made to protect the color of a floor that has been plastered, etc. It is spread out underneath, with a straw-mat spread out on top.”
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_397, pts-vp-en.2.242
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.4"
msgid "Cimilikaṃ vā uttarattharaṇaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā taṭṭikaṃ vā cammakhaṇḍaṃ vā pādapuñchaniṃ vā phalakapīṭhaṃ vā ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is a mat underlay, a blanket, a floor cover, a straw mat, a leather covering, a foot-wiping cloth, or a wooden bench, and he puts it out or gets it put out in the open, and he then leaves without putting it away or getting it put away or telling anyone, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.5"
msgid "Puggalike saṃghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.6"
msgid "Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.7"
msgid "Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.2.8"
msgid "Attano puggalike anāpatti."
msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc19, pts-cs-bu-pc14.2.3, ms2V_398
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.2"
msgid "uddharitvā gacchati,"
msgstr "if he leaves after putting it away;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.3"
msgid "uddharāpetvā gacchati,"
msgstr "if he leaves after getting it put away;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.4"
msgid "āpucchaṃ gacchati,"
msgstr "if he leaves after telling someone;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.5"
msgid "otāpento gacchati,"
msgstr "if he leaves while he is sunning it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.6"
msgid "kenaci palibuddhaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "if he is obstructed;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.7"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.8"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.9"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_399
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc14:2.3.10"
msgid "Senāsanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on furniture, is finished."
